{"id":"1212.4212","submitter":"Fabio Lorenzo Traversa Ph.D.","authors":"Fabio L. Traversa, Massimiliano Di Ventra, Fabrizio Bonani","title":"Generalized Floquet theory: application to dynamical systems with memory\n  and Bloch's theorem for nonlocal potentials","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Physical Review Letters, vol. 110, p. 170602, 2013","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.110.170602","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS math-ph math.MP nlin.CD","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Floquet theory is a powerful tool in the analysis of many physical phenomena,\nand extended to spatial coordinates provides the basis for Bloch's theorem.\nHowever, in its original formulation it is limited to linear systems with\nperiodic coefficients. Here, we extend the theory by proving a theorem for the\ngeneral class of systems including linear operators commuting with the\nperiod-shift operator. The present theorem greatly expands the range of\napplicability of Floquet theory to a multitude of phenomena that were\npreviously inaccessible with this type of analysis, such as dynamical systems\nwith memory. As an important extension, we also prove Bloch's theorem for\nnonlocal potentials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Dec 2012 02:18:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 23 Mar 2013 03:48:36 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 1 May 2013 23:44:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-05-03"}
